caption: The food was okay but not anything out of the ordinary. Although I made a reservation for a table I had to wait a bit for one to be available. Since I came during Chicago Restaurant week I ate from their prix fixe menu - It's nice that they included a drink! The margarita was good though the salt was on the side of the glass instead of on the rim. Everything else was just mediocre, the ceviche was more like a salad with dressing than a scoopable appetizer and I was unimpressed with the entrée presentation. The service was okay too - we had no napkins, no utensils, and they ran out of straws. I understand that it was busy but that's the bare minimum that should be on a table. If you're into a more contemporary vibe and don't care for traditional Latin American food, this is the place for you.
Food was meh. Good 2000s music Margheritas.
Amazing time here! The general manager is so nice, and the service was fantastic! I highly recommend the margaritas- they were absolutely delicious.
THE ABSOLUTE BEST TINGA CHICKEN TACOS IN ALL OF CHICAGO!!!!! I'M STRAIGHT ADDICTED NOW!

The hospitality and service is horrible and not worth the visit.I called hours in advance with reservations and waited 45 mins to be seated  and now unable to take advantage of Brunch menu as informed by the manger. Now being  seated and drinking our drinks and ordering food we sit and patiently wait  an hour before we ask the waiter for  an update on our food orders.The waiter then states that he hadn’t actually placed our food orders  because the “internet crashed”and no food was being prepared.To add  injury to insult the waiter then presents us with  a check that included the the food we NEVER  received .We confronted  the manger and the  bill was then adjusted.  I believe the lack of attention to service was due to myself and my party being Black .I state this because of the attention to detail the staff gave the non Black patrons,which included the brunch special after being seated after us and the   manger taking extra good care and attention to a group of young girls whom he also took  shots with.  Absolute TRASH!!

The staff are exceptional! All I wanted after a long day of exploring Chicago was a margarita, they went above and beyond my expectations. Sarah was beyond thoughtful! I ordered two margaritas - classic and coconut. Both were so delicious. Beware the coconut is a creamy one though.
Very subpar service.
I love brunch and bottomless mimosas here! Good food, great staff, nice atmosphere. Good for the girls day, or a day date

Food is just ok but the wait staff is really nice. Service was slow but managerially they were understaffed.  I’d likely go elsewhere for tacos in the future. Salsa portion was pretty small and the queso isn’t really conducive to dipping chips into - after 10 minutes, you’ll be cutting up the cheese to eat with a fork.  Nice location but won’t be back any time soon. Conveniently located near a Molly’s cupcakes.

If I could rate my experience here zero stars I would. My sister and I stopped here by chance for her to have a drink, I was the designated driver. After returning from the bathroom the general manager approached us. He lowered his mask to speak to us which was my first issue given we don't know him and our waitress kept her mask on for every interaction. His intention became quite clear when he proceeded to say inappropriate things and trying to hit on us when it was clearly not wanted and we were visibly uncomfortable. He proceeded to then speak into my ear asking me to to bend over. His actions made my skin crawl and in no way was welcomed by my sister and I. I will never step foot in this establishment again. I'm posting this to warn other women about his predatory behavior.

We waited an hour for our table even though we had a reservation. The servers were really nice and the food was decent but their brunch menu was very limited and you have to pick a brunch item to get bottomless mimosas.

We had just finished our last final and came to Bar Takito to hang out and relax. The vibe is a great experience the bartenders are fun and chill to talk with! We especially had such a good time with Raphael!!! Such a sweet and kind soul. Marco was also so nice, witty, and very professional! Definitely coming back next time we are celebrating anything.
Great service!
The steak tacos are good but the coconut rice I would steer clear of. I love coconut but something was throwing me off with it.
Awesome place
Great tacos and good sized entrees. Cheese cake was also excellent.
Food delightful 😋 Service excellent 👏🏽 Recommend trying every single taco & the arepa 🫓 won’t regret anything!
Love this place!! The bartender Marco is really nice!! We have so much fun here all the time

Food and drinks were both delicious. Hsv to sit outside, so it was a bit chilly, but the tacos made it so worth it. The steak and pork belly tacos were on point. The margaritas were delicious as but a bit pricey. I will def go back again. Thanks for a good first visit!
Really good food and drinks and the tacos along with outdoor seating,  greats service

Great time here, everything was delicious and the drinks were great. Will be back in the future.

Pretty good, but not amazing. The tacos were on the smaller side, so definitely don't stop with just 2!

Cute place. Good service. Food was okay. 4/5 for ambiance and experience overall. We each got an arepa plate for brunch and pineapple 🍍 guacamole and chips. I got a yummy 🍉 watermelon marg and my friend got a good Paloma.

Drinks are flame... don't know about the food...
Currently open with outdoor seating.  They serve really good margaritas

Drinks were good but food was mediocre. Service was just ok.
Their brunch was worth it! My.server went about and beyond when he noticed my eggs were not cooked properly. You have to try their guacamole and chips, because it had me ready to order secods.

Food was very basic and lacking flavor. As for drinks,  Mojitos and Palomas were decent but Margaritas were very syrupy. Probably won't be giving this place a second try.
TERRIBLE service! I wish I could give zero stars if I could. Very unprofessional establishment. Will not be going back. Food was mediocre.

Even though a few others had already stated their complaints/experience with either the hostess or waiters, I can’t help but agree but what is more surprising is the response from the owner themselves on certain reviews. Shows how much this place and the owner lack in customer service!!!! Horrible.

Went to bar Takito for a brunch about two weeks ago with my daughter and some friends and unfortunately the experience was not super pleasant. The waiter was not pleasant at all and made it pretty uncomfortable to be there. Unfortunately I will not be back as Customer Service is a big deal.
I was wondering why our waiter Chris was inattentive and rude. Then I saw the tip was included on check. Not helpful and looked like he wanted to be elsewhere.

First time here with my coworkers for a dinner that was planned some time ago. The food was planned ahead of time and I am so happy that it was because it was nice not have to think about what to order. We had the trio of guacamole and I fell in love with the chips... they were pretty big which allowed for more guacamole to be eaten. We had so many tacos on our table... steak, pork belly and coconut shrimp - which was my favorite! And we also had their coconut rice which was the perfect balance of sweet and savory.  When we first got there though, my coworker, that planned this dinner, and I had some aqua fresca (watermelon and the blood orange) and we ordered some octopus a la plancha. The octopus looked good on the plate when we received it but when we started eating it, it was surely overcooked because it was rubbery.  Also, the bartender wasn't that friendly... treated us like we weren't worth his time. I don't understand why he acted so cold to myself and my coworker. But whatever... we knew that we weren't going to be working with him once our tables were ready.  I might make the trip with some friends and the hubby to try it out again another time.

Our waiter was amazing, however the hostess was extremely rude and made my friends and I want to leave. We already had a reservation and since it was Friday night we couldn’t find anywhere else to go, so we decided to stay. I showed her my open table reservation and she told me we would have to wait at least 30 minutes for a table even though there where maybe 4-5 tables available on top of having my reservation. I told her that can’t be right because I see empty tables and we came 5 minutes before our reservation. She then proceeded to roll her eyes at me and grabbed our menus without saying anything and tossed them on the table next to her and told us to sit. I then saw her and the other hostess making faces while looking at our table. I have never experienced that kind of treatment before. If she wanted to talk about us she could’ve gone to the back. After our dinner which was okay( the waiter was super respectful) I came up to her and asked her for her name. She looked me in the eyes and said “umm no” and walked away. Overall I will definitely not be coming back. Although the food and waiter were great, coming into an establishment and getting that kind of treatment from a person who’s job it is to make you feel welcome made me never want to come back. There are so many places in the city that are much more professional and I would recommend going ANYWHERE else because receiving this kind of treatment from a place where you are paying for their service is unacceptable.

Phenomenal experience, the bartenders were very friendly and accommodating, the Tacos were amazing and the margaritas were on point. Nice to find a very a place like this while traveling. Highly Recommend.

Waited 20 minutes to get seated despite having a reservation. Waiter was rude and demeaning. Service was slow. My friend’s order was forgotten and he waited an extra 20 minutes to get food after everyone else, yet no one apologized in the slightest. I am trying to think of a worse service experience but my memory escapes me.

Went to Bar Takito last Saturday for a birthday brunch. Very disappointing considering how good the reviews are. Our waiter’s name was Chris and he was less than friendly. He was very cold and didn’t even crack a smile. When we were all seated, he told my group to move in a rude manner because our table was close to the table next to us, even though no one was sitting at the table next to us. We brought up the free birthday margarita that’s advertised online and again, he rudely responds “you have to give your email and I have to see the link” then left the table. We eventually figured it out without his help and received the free drink because now at this point it’s just principle. The arepa benedict was very bland but on the bright side, the chilaquiles are decent. The place is super cute but unfortunately will never go back thanks to Chris.

Food is delicious!!
Portions were on the small side, but very creative. The tequila flights were well priced and the service and atmosphere were excellent.

We were really excited to try the menu. We were greeted by a bus boy with waters and to tell us their new drink menu had debuted. Lots of servers hanging out by the kitchen and host stand, we couldn’t even flag someone down. 20 minutes and no service, we left.

Overall: A perfect spot for a happy hour featuring margaritas and delicious tacos.  The good: Arguably some of the best tacos I’ve had in awhile, and beats overhyped places like Big and Little’s. The crispy fish and coconut shrimp, both on blue corn tortillas, were amazing in their own way. The fish had a tangy and unique sauce paired with it, and the shrimp was paired with a tasty dollops of a honey sauce. Additionally, the esquites were amazing! The corn was roasted well without being overcooked, and it was a great balance between the cheeses and sauces, so nothing was runny. And, I can’t go without saying how great the margs were. Refreshing, strong, and delicious.  The not-so-good: While great, the tacos are a bit pricey. $9-12 (depending on which you get) for 2 tacos, which are on the small side, is a bit much. Also, we were sitting outside, and the train can be a bother (not that that’s something they can change). And, the entire inside smelled like cleaning solution, and it crept outside at times as well.  Food/Drink: 9/10 Atmosphere: 8/10 Service: 8/10

Really disappointed by the value.  The guac and chips were ~$10 and included ~8 chips and guac that lined the bowl vs consisted of any depth.  No part of that appetizer was worth $10. Went here for a 2 year olds birthday party. The inappropriateness of this venue for that event aside, the planning by the bar could have been better. If it was a different event, I suppose it might have been an okay location. Also, the table area on the platform near the windows. OMG. That iron foot rest in front of the platform has got to go! Not only kids but many adults tripped on that thing.

The food is a 4 but the service was a terror!  If you want to see what it looks like for a server to think they’re too good to serve others and work then this is the perfect place to come. Asked for queso and the server rolled her eyes at me then said they don’t have that, when the menu had queso sauce as a dishes ingredient clearly printed. My friend asked for a hot sauce and got another eye roll. Finally got the queso after three times of asking and pointing it out on the menu. The tacos are okay but the menu has lots of rules which is odd, you should be able to have what you ask for if you’re willing to pay. Margaritas were good but very expensive and alot of ice!

I LOVED this place! I suggested it to my husband and sister-in-law and they were skeptical.  I saw this place on a "driveby" to the Ventra office. I told my husband we should try it. My picky eater of a daughter ate everything we picked! Mack, our server was AWESOME!!! He requested to prepare a non-alcoholic drink for my daughter (she's 9) and she totally appreciated it! The food was great; the service was poor.  Reservation for nine people. There are only 8 place settings. I asked if the table would be enough space for 9 people and plates and cups and things? The hostess asked, “Well, are your friends all large people?”  WHAT kind of response is that? For one thing, yes, three of them are. Thank you for fat-shaming my friends.  Another friend ordered soda water and it took 20 minutes to receive it.  The staff wasn’t terribly attentive or hospitable.

My family visited this restaurant tonight for my moms 60th bday. We had a full day downtown in the heat and had just seen Hamilton and we weren’t looking for anything too fancy. This place was perfect! I was able to get a reservation for 8 plus a high chair. When we got there we sat at a higher table with stools, but my niece  wasn’t able to reach the top of the table in her high chair. I asked if they could move us to a shorter table and they did! I very much appreciated them accommodating us. I would have loved to give them 5 stars but I just wasn’t much impressed with the portion sizes for shared plates. The octopus was perfect for our group size, but the ceviche trio (way overpriced for what you get), guac & Chips and rice did not stretch very far. All in all, it’s a great place with great food and definitely worth checking out!
The food was amazing!   My family shared several plates,  and every one was excellent. We'll definitely return!

Came here during a weekday happy hour, which actually was from 3:30-6PM, not 5:30. And as long as you order before 6PM, you'd have the happy hour price.  I ordered the steak taco which was quite good. I liked the purple potato chip that was topped off. I probably would have purchased those chips just as an appetizer if there was the option to.  The restaurant was very modern and great for groups since they had large tables and were able to take multiple credit cards - though they weren't able to split checks which I always prefer.  Service was great, water was always refilled, and the taking of orders was prompt.  I'm only giving this 3 stars because while the food and service was good, I don't think I'd come back on my own. The pricing of the tacos, even during happy hour were $3 for a 2 bite taco. Not the most budget friendly establishment but I can see people coming here for good drinks and food if they don't mind the cost much.

The chips were average. The French fries was a bit insulting as it was a portion of a potato and such a high price. The dessert was in a tiny shot glass that was flan with caramel. It tasted exactly how it sounds but a bit sweeter. I would say go here and give this place a try for fun.
